## Why This Is Asked

Tests ability to design end-to-end CAPA workflow for data privacy policy failures, including evidence capture and cross-tenant rollout.

## Key Concepts

- CAPA data modeling for evidence and artifacts
- Lifecycle state machine and ownership
- Minimal REST API design with linked logs/traces
- Tenant/region metrics for containment and recurrence
- RCA templates and canary rollout planning

## Code Example

```javascript
// CAPA core types (overview)
interface CAPA {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  evidence: string[];
  artifacts: string[];
  state: 'detected'|'triaged'|'in_progress'|'contained'|'closed';
  createdAt: string;
  updatedAt?: string;
  links?: { type: string; url: string }[];
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you scale CAPA data stores across regions?
- How to ensure regulatory auditability and evidence integrity?

Why This Is Asked
Tests end-to-end CAPA thinking for distributed streaming with event-ordering issues and rollback safety.

Key Concepts
- CAPA data model for evidence and artifacts
- Lifecycle state machine with containment and prevention
- Minimal REST API for linking logs/traces to CAPAs
- Region/shard-aware metrics and attribution correctness
- RCA template and canary rollback strategy

Code Example
```javascript
// Minimal REST API sketch (Express)
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
app.use(express.json());
app.post('/caps', (req, res) => {
  // validate and persist CAPA with evidence refs
  res.status(201).send({ id: 'capa-123' });
});
```

Follow-up Questions
- How would you validate and test the canary rollback under varying traffic patterns?
- What data retention and privacy controls are needed for CAPA artifacts?
